7            Establishing and Maintaining the Environment

This section describes how an organization establishes and maintains EPPORA’s environment.  It discusses how projects are created, user attributes specified, new labor categories created, customized calendars and project ranking criteria are specified.  It also includes describing how general options are selected and maintained.  The establishing/maintaining of the environment is accomplished by Administrators, Project Managers, Business Analysts and Project Portfolio Managers.

7.1    Users Page

An Administrator establishes a user’s initial attributes.  The user’s attributes are maintained by Project Portfolio Managers, the user’s Supervisor and the users themselves.  An Executive establishes and updates the user’s salary. An Administrator opens the “Users Page” shown in Figures 9-11. Each user must be at least one “User Type” and can be multiple user types. The Users Page is invoked from the Administration tab “Create User,” “Delete User” and “Update User” commands.  Depending on which command is selected along with the user type of the individual that is specifying the command, different objects within the page are displayed.  Both the “Update User” and “Delete User” invoke the “Select User” page shown in Figure 11c.

Figure 9—Create Users Page

Figure 10—Delete Users Page

Figure 11a—Update Users Initial Page

Figure 11b-Update Users Attributes Page

 

The selection of a user invokes the “User Selection” page.  This occurs when a user is selected for the “Users Update,” the “Users Delete” page and the “Supervisor” button shown in Figure 11b.  It also occurs in numerous other pages where one or more users are needed.  If only a single user is needed, EPPORA selects the highlighted user or if no user is highlighted, than the topmost user in the User List object.  Users can be selected from the User Type, if none are specified than all user types are selected, the labor categories associated with a user or the initial letter of a user’s name.

7.5    Triggers Page

An integral part of EPPORA is its ability to diagnose potentially dangerous conditions that affect a project’s budget, scope or schedule.  Each of the triggers, when they occur, causes EPPORA to send mail to a designated set of users.  Triggers usually automatically send mail to the relevant Project Manager and Project Portfolio Manager.  A few triggers send mail to Administrators and Executives.  Each trigger has a default as to when an mail will be sent.  In addition, the Administrator or the Project Portfolio Manager can specify a set of users that the trigger’s mail should be sent to when it occurs and the type of mail, either standard email or EPPORA’s internal mail. Figure 16 is the “Triggers” Page used to establish the “Trigger” options. The Triggers Page is invoked from the Administration menu using the “Triggers” command.

7.8    Requirements Page

The Requirements Page is used to create a project’s requirements.  Figure 19 shows an example “Requirements” Page.  When you initially begin specifying the requirements for a project (assuming you are either the project’s Project Manager or a Project Portfolio Manager) there will be no entries under either the “Req’t ID” or the “Title.”  All the radio buttons will be in the off state.  To insert a requirement, you press the “Insert” button and set the “Insert-Before” or “Insert-After” radio button.  The requirement will be inserted before or after the selected requirement. The “Requirements” Page is invoked from the Project Page.

8.13  Backup Page

EPPORA supports the manual backing up and restoring of data.  Each created backup is placed in the directory C:\EPPORA\Backup.  The file name is a concatenation of the text string “EPPORA-Backup” followed by the project’s name followed by a “-“ and then followed by the date and time in the following format yyyy-mmm-dd-hh-mm-ss, where ‘yyyy’ represents the year, ‘mmm’ represents the month, ‘dd’ represents the day, ‘hh’ represents the hour, ‘mm’ represents the minute and ‘ss’ represents the seconds.  Only an Administrator can perform a backup.
